      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Few of these looks close to a win. ZOU ZOU KAPADOKIA (7) has placed twice and both in soft ground. Closed off strongly last start to get up for third, beaten a head, over 1350m at Ipswich and should be winding up late again.  BACIAMI (1) ran above expectations and got up for third at big odds at his latest appearance at Eagle Farm over 1300m. Kyle Wilson-Taylor stays aboard and although yet to win has been in the money on two occasions. Fitter and a likely improver. MOTIVATING (3) missed the placings two runs back then got a long way back last start when 4.5 lengths away in seventh over 1350m at Ipswich. Perfectly placed and is sure to take a ton of beating. STEVENTOWN (5) was unplaced two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1350m at Ipswich, beaten 2.75 lengths into fifth. Wound up strongly from the back and can run into the finish here. YELLOW CRATE (8) next best.",
